<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="423" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="423">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="423">
Body length 4.5-6 mm. Spots on pronotum in shape of narrow stripes (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 1–2" captionStartId="F1" captionText="Figure 1 - 2. 1 Dorsal habitus of male Berosus (s. str.) geminus from Yaroslavl Oblast, Russia. 2 Aedagus. A - lateral view, B - side view." httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/472150" pageId="0" pageNumber="423">1</figureCitation>
). First abdominal ventrite with small longitudinal keel on the base. Elytral apex rounded, without spine. Interval 4 of elytra with regular row of punctures, bigger punctures visible on elytra interval 3 only. At the sides of elytra - a clear and isolated spot (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 1–2" captionStartId="F1" captionText="Figure 1 - 2. 1 Dorsal habitus of male Berosus (s. str.) geminus from Yaroslavl Oblast, Russia. 2 Aedagus. A - lateral view, B - side view." httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/472150" pageId="0" pageNumber="423">1</figureCitation>
). Aedeagus as in Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 1–2" captionStartId="F1" captionText="Figure 1 - 2. 1 Dorsal habitus of male Berosus (s. str.) geminus from Yaroslavl Oblast, Russia. 2 Aedagus. A - lateral view, B - side view." httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/472150" pageId="0" pageNumber="423">2</figureCitation>
</paragraph>
